node.text:
Huge Expansion: Avianca Reveals 23 New Routes Across The Americas⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Today, Avianca announced the launch of 23 new international routes from five different Latin American countries. Colombia will have 13 new point-to-point connections, Ecuador and Costa Rica will have four each, and El Salvador and Guatemala one each. Let’s investigate further.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Getty Images⁠
⁠

node.text:
United’s CEO Doesn’t See Mandatory Vaccines For Domestic Travel⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
United Airlines CEO Scott Kirby has once again spoken out regarding mandatory vaccination. This time, Kirby confirmed that he does not believe vaccines will be mandatory for domestic travel within the US. The comment came one day after Kirby met with President Biden to discuss mandatory vaccinations.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Denver International Airport⁠
⁠

node.text:
Boeing's Alaska Airlines 737 MAX ecoDemonstrator Starts Testing⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
The latest installment of the Boeing ecoDemonstrator seems to be in full swing as a modified Boeing 737 MAX darts around the skies surrounding Seattle. Using an aircraft bound for Alaska Airlines after testing, Boeing is attempting to make flying safer and more sustainable by testing new initiatives. ⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Preston Fiedler⁠
⁠

node.text:
Start Of An Era: JetBlue Touches Down In London Heathrow⁠
⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Last night, JetBlue Flight B620 left New York JFK to land at London Heathrow just over seven hours later at 09:36 EDT this morning. Simple Flying was there to welcome the hybrid carrier to the United Kingdom as it celebrated the inauguration of its transatlantic flights.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: JetBlue⁠
⁠

node.text:
Lufthansa Retrieves A Boeing 747-400 From Desert Storage ⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Lufthansa has withdrawn another Boeing 747-400 from storage ahead of the type's anticipated return to service. This time, the airline looked to its collection of widebody aircraft at the Teruel aircraft storage site in the Spanish desert. ⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Oliver Rösler via Lufthansa⁠
⁠

node.text:
Singapore Airlines Relaunches US 5th Freedom Flight After 13 Years ⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
An old fifth freedom route is being revived by Singapore Airlines, connecting Taipei to Los Angeles. However, given the current travel restrictions, the route will no be bookable right through. Nevertheless, it adds one more option to those flying between the two countries, as well as valuable cargo capacity. The route is set to launch on August 25th. ⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Singapore Airlines⁠
⁠

node.text:
Avianca Won’t Take Any New Aircraft Until 2024⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Avianca Holdings has just filed its Chapter 11 plan, and it has shown the immediate future for the company once it exits its bankruptcy proceedings. United Airlines will continue as Avianca’s leading partner (along with Copa Airlines), and we could see many new aircraft entering the airline in the next decade. Let’s investigate further. ⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Getty Images⁠
⁠

node.text:
Allegiant’s Huge Network Expansion Sees 22 Routes Added ⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Allegiant is to begin a further 22 routes this year, with only two previously served by the ultra-low-cost carrier (ULCC). It has also revealed two new bases at Appleton and Flint with a total of five stationed A320s, helping to cement the future of these airports. With just one of Allegiant’s coming 22 routes to see head-to-head competition, we delve into what’s happening.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Allegiant⁠
⁠

node.text:
The Most Notable New Airline Routes This Week ⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Qatar Airways launched its next two African destinations on August 6th, with Lusaka and Harare taking off. Running three-weekly, QR1455 departs Doha at 02:20, arrives at Lusaka at 08:50, departs at 10:10, and arrives in Harare an hour later.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Kenneth Kaunda International Airport⁠

node.text:
Virgin Eyes Scotland With First Long Haul Flights From Edinburgh ⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Virgin Atlantic has revealed an exciting move to bring its long-haul services to Scotland. The airline will begin flying from Edinburgh to Barbados on December 5th, operating a twice-weekly service between the Sottish capital and the Caribbean. Next year, the airline plans to add a route to Orlando from Edinburgh, firming up its position at the Scottish airport.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Airbus⁠
⁠

node.text:
Ryanair Counts For A Third Of Boeing’s July 2021 Deliveries ⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Ryanair accounted for roughly 1/3 of Boeing’s total aircraft output for July 2021. The airline took delivery of nine out of 28 aircraft delivered by the US aerospace giant during the month. With deliveries of the Boeing 787 still at a standstill, the manufacturer failed to compete with rival Airbus, who shipped 47 aircraft during the month.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Getty Images⁠
⁠

node.text:
Etihad Airways Cuts Its 1st Half Loss By 50%⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Etihad Airways has revealed its accounts for the first half of 2021. While the outcome was still negative overall, the losses have been significantly trimmed to some 50% of where they were during the same period last year. The airline said that the results represent a ‘progressive recovery’, and that it is preparing for a tidal wave of demand once restrictions are relaxed.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Vincenzo Pace | Simple Flying | @jfkjetsofficial⁠
⁠
